      {"op": "add_text", "slide_index": 15, "text": "Market window is closing\nCompetitive consolidation expected within 2-3 years as the market approaches $15-20B. Early movers in regulated markets build durable advantages.\n\nRegulatory tailwinds\nIndonesia, Vietnam, and Thailand are all implementing pro-digital policies. Regulatory frameworks are stabilizing, reducing compliance uncertainty.\n\nPlatform readiness\nOur localization and compliance modules are production-ready. Delaying entry means competitors can close the gap.\n\nCost of delay\nEach 6-month delay reduces projected Year 3 market share by 3-4 points, equivalent to ~$8M in annual revenue.", "left": 6.7, "top": 2.9, "width": 5.3, "height": 3.2, "font_size": 12, "font_color": "575757"},

      {"op": "add_notes", "slide_index": 15, "text": "This is the decision slide. Framing: (1) We are asking for $45M phased over 3 years with stage gates — this is NOT an all-or-nothing commitment. (2) Year 1 tranche of $20M covers Foundation and Launch phases. Board reviews progress before releasing Year 2 funds. (3) Emphasize the cost of inaction: each 6-month delay costs ~$8M in Year 3 revenue because the market is consolidating. (4) Our platform is ready today — the constraint is capital and local execution, not technology. Anticipated objections: 'Why not start with one country?' — Response: regulatory filing timelines mean we need to start Vietnam/Thailand processes in parallel even if Indonesia launches first. Sequential approach adds 18 months to full-market timeline."},

